{"id":"project-LICHEN-te9m","title":"router.c: Missing NULL check for dst_iid parameter in route_mesh_local path","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/router.c
Lines: 230-249

In lichen_router_route(), the function validates dst_addr but not dst_iid:

    if (router == NULL || dst_addr == NULL || result == NULL) {
        return -EINVAL;
    }

Then at line 249:
    return route_mesh_local(router, dst_iid, now_ms, result);

If dst_iid is NULL and the address is classified as LICHEN_ADDR_MESH_LOCAL, the code passes NULL to route_mesh_local() which then passes it to lichen_gradient_lookup() where it will be dereferenced by memcmp.

The dst_iid parameter should be validated at the top of the function along with the other pointer parameters.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:49:33.003562Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:49:33.003589Z"}
